<note id="fs-id1167832075518">
<title>Vertical and Horizontal Lines</title>
<para id="fs-id1167832152868">A <emphasis effect="bold">vertical line</emphasis> is the graph of an equation of the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1167834395223"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mspace width="12em"/></m:mrow></m:math>The line passes through the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>-axis at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1167835421545">A <emphasis effect="bold">horizontal line</emphasis> is the graph of an equation of the form <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1167835367829"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mspace width="12em"/></m:mrow></m:math>The line passes through the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-axis at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</note>
<example id="fs-id1167831872404">
