</media></para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1167831959139" class="material-set-2">
<problem id="fs-id1167831959141">
<para id="fs-id1167831920778"><span class="token">ⓐ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓑ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−2</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓒ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓓ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−4</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> <span class="token">ⓔ</span> <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mn>7</m:mn><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<para id="fs-id1167835390387">In the following exercises, for each ordered pair, decide</para>
<para id="fs-id1167835309845"><span class="token">ⓐ</span> is the ordered pair a solution to the equation? <span class="token">ⓑ</span> is the point on the line?</para>
<exercise id="fs-id1167834516106" class="material-set-2">
<problem id="fs-id1167834516108">
<para id="fs-id1167834516111"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>;</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math><newline/>A: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>;</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> B: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>;</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> C: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−1</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>;</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> D: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mn>−3</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>−1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<media id="fs-id1167832042287" alt="This figure shows a straight line graphed on the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y-axes run from negative 8 to 8. The line goes through the points (negative 3, negative 1), (negative 2, 0), (negative 1, 1), (0, 2), (1, 3), (2, 4), and (3, 5).">
